<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-06-06T07:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-06-06T07:00:00-05:00" n="200" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d200">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 893.51/926.</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Ambassador to
                                        Germany</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss></hi>.</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                                        <hi rend="italic">Berlin</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-06-06T13:00:00+01:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">June 6, 1912—1 p.m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>Paris forwards your May 17 and May 24. The German Government is in
                                accord with your expressed views and has so informed the German
                                banking group. Some opposition is being shown by England and France,
                                especially to Austrian participation, and I believe that this is
                                also shared by German bankers. The German Government has expressed
                                no views as to preliminary advances, their disposition being to
                                leave this question to the financial groups.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Leishman.</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>